author: Russell Brand
description:
Go to http://polymarket.com to trade on the outcomes of live events from politics, pop culture, to sports and more!


Can Britain still be called a liberal democracy as facial recognition, digital ID, programmable money, and mass surveillance are quietly fused into a single system of control? This discussion examines how tools sold as safety and convenience become permanent infrastructure, how anonymity and dissent are reframed as disorder, and how party politics masks a deeper continuity of power. The focus isn’t one policy or one government, but the construction of a surveillance state that functions regardless of who’s in office. The question is whether democracy survives in substance, or only in name, once compliance becomes the price of everyday life.
